tool_description: Retrieve all the data from ArtStation including Projects, Artists, Jobs, Prints and Magazine Posts .
title: ArtStation

api_list.name: Magazine Posts
api_list.code:
import requests

url = "https://artstation.p.rapidapi.com/magazine/posts"

headers = {
    "X-RapidAPI-Key": "SIGN-UP-FOR-KEY",
    "X-RapidAPI-Host": "artstation.p.rapidapi.com"
}

response = requests.get(url, headers=headers)

print(response.json())

data.title: Future Bike
data.description:
I did this mostly to design out the bike. It's something I have been toying with for a project. No time to develop it properly at the moment so I sketched out the rough idea here.

I think this one was around 2-3 hours. Focusing on keeping things super simple. Process steps show the basic way it was created. Lots of details made up in the line phase.

data.title: Sake Barrels
data.description:
Inspired by the Meiji Shrine in Tokyo.
Made in Substance Designer, rendered with Marmoset.

Achieving a faithful recreation of the reference material proved to be quite the challenge - especially when it came to identifying the kanji. I must extend a huge thank-you to RÃªverain on the Japanese and English Chat Discord server for assisting me in this - without their help and expertise, my translations would have been riddled with mistakes!

data.title: Dying Light 2
data.description:
Blast from the past Little celebration of Dying Light 2 release!

Back in 2016-2019 I worked on Dying Light 2 as a concept artist. That was my first project I worked on. After such a long time it is good to see the game out ! All the best to the team and good job delivering the game <3
